metadata.name: Duet #59
metadata.description:
by Daeinc
Aug 2022

Duet explores generative+computational motion and creates an almost infinite sequence of visual compositions. Two groups of shapes transform, merge, and split randomly. What can be disorienting starts to make sense as every element is animated from one to the other. This transition animation is what connects random pieces and creates a relationship between them. Each element is mathematically interpolated, with its motion defined by an equation. 

Although there are key moments, it is hard to summarize time-based work as a static image. As a constantly evolving generative motion piece, Duet invites viewers to form their impression by feeling the rhythm over time.

## Guide:
- The animation responds to window aspect ratio. It reproduces the same outcome at the same ratio. 
- For reliable playback, keep the window active and use IPFS view.
- See browser console for more info.
- Tested on MacOS 12.5.1 with Chromium 104.0

## Keyboard Interaction
- [n] to play a new random loop.
- [spacebar] to play/pause.
- [s] to save PNG. use URL params for dimensions.
- [up] and [down] to change shape resolution.
- [left] and [right] to change BPM. only works while looping. 
- [h] to toggle high DPI mode. off by default.
- [p] to toggle pixel snapping. off by default.

## URL Parameters
- add parameters separated by ampersand to the URL ex. https://.../?fxhash=...&w=1200&h=600
- [w] and [h]: set width and height in pixels. (ex. w=1200&h=600)
- [s] and [e]: set starting and ending keyframes (inclusive) for loop. (ex. s=20&e=24) 
- setting large values for start/end is not advised.
- [len]: instead of start/end, set a loop length between 1 and 16. (ex. len=4)
- [bpm]: beats per minute. (ex. bpm=80)
- [res]: shape resolution between 0 and 18. (ex. res=2)
- [pr]: pixel ratio. set it to 2 (or press [h]) for hi-DPI screens.
- [ar]: maximum aspect ratio. set to any value over 1. 1.2 by default.
- [snap]: add the param to snap to pixel grid.

## License
CC BY-NC 4.0
Please refer to the included LICENSE.md for license information.
Libraries used: canvas-sketch, canvas-sketch-util, dom-events, hsv2rgb, keyframes, equations from easings.net, array shuffle from stackoverflow.

metadata.description:
Just an ordinary scene from a typical day, working as a Sprocket Factory engineer. Inspiration for this work is drawn from the composable nature of blockchain smart contracts and the flow of value between networks of autonomous machines and free-willed individuals.

"A Doodle, Ringer, and Fidenza walk into a Space Bar..."

- Press "S" to export an SVG vector.

metadata.name: Garden Of Symmetry #129
metadata.description:
Sometimes, things look better when seen from the distance. Not from far away, but from a length that allows one to see what’s possibly underneath. Or, you may not see anything. Instead, you can just enjoy things falling into place.

Get a pack of shattered glass, snow, or ice*, uncovering a pattern. Or an axis of dancing geometries. Enter the Garden of Symmetry.

The graphic is a plottable SVG file in A3 format, ready to be drawn using a pen plotter. In the full screen view, click somewhere on the artwork to download a copy.

I recommend to optimize the SVG before plotting, i.e. using vpype. I also recommend to draw the graphic using 0.7mm pen.

License: CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/ - @jakub_antolak

———

metadata.name: Solid Line #65
metadata.description:
Solid Line is made of square tiles with predefined patterns, disposed randomly, and on top of which is drawn a line. By isolating the colors, this line creates a new structure of seemingly interlaced shapes.

There are three possible level of details, and a rare "Outline" feature that will render only the line layer.

SVG generated with JavaScript.

The SVG can be saved by pressing "s" on the full-screen view.
A PNG version can be exported by pressing "e" on the full-screen view.

By default the dimensions of the export are 6000×8000.
These dimensions can be changed by adding, for example, ?w=12000 to the full-screen page URL, where w is the desired width. Then press "e" to export at this size.

metadata.name: Millefoglie #394
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ​[mil fœj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Carême.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (pâte feuilletée), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (crème pâtissière). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." — Wikipedia

Prints available upon request: prints@stefancontiero.com
Best enjoyed on browsers supporting Display-P3 color gamut.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

@stefan_contiero

metadata.name: Interdimensional Highways II #124
metadata.description:
Since the discovery of the first Interdimensional Highway, we have been getting better at charting them and improving our understanding of how they function. But we must hurry, because as we continue to prepare our vehicles, our bodies and minds for this one of a kind travel, there's still one question that remains to be answered:

Which will be our fate: to conquer... or to be conquered?

Interdimensional Highways is a two-parts series of generative artwork, showing some of the possible formations of connecting ways between multiple dimensions.

* * *

9 reserved pieces will be sent as gift to collectors who minted 4 or more pieces of Interdimensional Highways I.

Press S to save as PNG.

Made by: yenren / twitter.com/yenrenART
Made with: JavaScript + HTML Canvas
License: LICENSE.txt

metadata.name: Morixel Colab #7 Generative Mirza #1
metadata.description:
This series is an interactive character creation project with the audience using computer programming. 
Thus, every time the Collector presses the create button on the site, a new character is born in the form of a member of the updated family of Qajar and this paradox of tradition and modernity provides a humorous atmosphere. which makes him smile and this event is our most important request.

If you like, give a name to your character and share it with us

The Generative Mirza is unique random Generated 200 PFP NFTs. The number of Traits in this collection is 10 (89 layers) and it has the ability to make unique 606,528,000 NFTs.

To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

This project is a collaboration project and it is a Benefit for the owners of most Morixels to Collaborate with Morixels Designer.

You can read more information on Morixels website 👇

Website: https://morixels.com/

Twitter: @Morixels

by: @morteza_yousefy & @MontazeriAmin

Made in 2022

metadata.name: The Living Book #2 Moonrise #40
metadata.description:
I have been exploring the medium of print for years. Mixing etching, silk-screening, offset, photocopy, risography, drawing and painting to design and craft experimental art books.From the day digital, which had always fascinated me, took over my publishing practice, I always liked to create bridges between these two worlds.

The Living Books is part of this series of hybrid and experimental works where paper and digital resonate.

This issue #2 is made of 64 pages that will be minted by collectors. A book will eventually be printed and the pages will follow the mint order. Each page exists in a cover version (c) and a xerox version (x).

Controls :

• Click to dive into each frame.
• Press C to toggle cover mode.
• Press X to toggle xerox mode.
• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

The Living Book #2 Moonrise by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity
